P.title: Will a member of the Trump family be the Republican nominee for the US Presidency in 2024?
P.body:
Resolution Criteria
Resolves Yes if one of these individuals is the Republican nominee for the US Presidency in 2024:
Donald Trump
Donald Trump Jr.
Eric Trump
Ivanka Trump
Tiffany Trump
Melania Trump
Barron Trump

Q.title: Will we detect an exoplanet atmosphere with >5% oxygen atmosphere before 2030?
Q.body:
Resolution Criteria
This question will resolve as Yes if any exoplanet with >5% O2 atmosphere is found before January 1, 2030

Q_and_not_P.title: Will we detect an exoplanet atmosphere with >5% oxygen and will the event occur before 2030?
Q_and_not_P.body:
Resolution Criteria
This question will resolve as Yes if both of the following occur: (1) an exoplanet with >5% O2 atmosphere is found before January 1, 2030 and (2) the event described in the second question occurs.

Q.title: Will the existence and smoothness properties of the Navier-Stokes equations in three dimensions turn out to depend on the compactness of the universe over which they are defined?
Q.body:
Resolution Criteria
This question resolves positively if before the resolution date of the question there are proofs of either both A and D or both B and C. It resolves negatively if there are proofs of either both A and B or both C and D. If neither event takes place before the resolution date of the question, the question resolves ambiguously

Q_and_not_P.title: Will both of the following occur: (1) Will the existence and smoothness properties of the Navier-Stokes equations in three dimensions turn out to depend on the compactness of the universe over which they are defined? (2) Will the question QsMaMRdcErTvrTeACTTK be resolved positively?
Q_and_not_P.body:
Resolution Criteria
This question resolves positively if before the resolution date of the question there are proofs of either both A and D or both B and C regarding the Navier-Stokes equations. It resolves negatively if there are proofs of either both A and B or both C and D. If neither event takes place before the resolution date of the question, the question resolves ambiguously. Additionally, the question QsMaMRdcErTvrTeACTTK will also be taken into account in determining the overall resolution.
